          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-02-14 22:43:03" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(a figurative extension of meaning of σπιλάς ‘a rock or reef washed by the sea,’ not occurring in the NT) an unrecognized source of danger or peril</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>unseen danger</Gloss>
                <Gloss>hidden danger</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>σπιλάς in {S:06500101200016} may also be understood as meaning ‘spot’ or ‘stain’ (see {D:79.57}).</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
